==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impearl
<hw>Im*pearl"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Impearled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Impearling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>im-</ets>
in + <ets>pearl</ets>: cf. F. <ets>emperler</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To form into pearls, or into that which resembles pearls.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dewdrops which the sun⟦br⟧
<qex>Impearls</qex> on every leaf and every flower.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To decorate as with pearls or with anything
resembling pearls.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With morning dews <qex>impearled</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The dews of the morning <qex>impearl</qex> every thorn.</q>
<rj><qau>R. Digby.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impeccability</ent>⟦br⟧
